            <title>[GROOVY-386] continue in switch generates verificartion error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-386</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;i  = 0&lt;br/&gt;
while (true) {&lt;br/&gt;
	i++;&lt;br/&gt;
	switch&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
{
		case 3:
			continue 
		case 5:
			break
	}
&lt;p&gt;	System.out.println&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
	if (i ==10) break;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The continue keyword works if put outside of the switch&lt;/p&gt;</description>
